passengers used emergency chutes to exit an 
american airlines jetliner saturday after smoke was seen coming 
from the planes landing gear an airline official said 
there were no injuries to the 46 passengers and five crew 
members on board flight 1333 said american airlines spokesman tom 
stack 
the mcdonnell douglas md80 was taxiing down the runway at 
ohare international airport after landing from grand rapids 
mich when the pilot of a plane behind it reported seeing smoke 
coming from the left main landing gear stack said 
the pilot of flight 1333 ordered passengers to evacuate the 
plane by the chute slides as a precautionary measure stack said 
an initial inspection of the plane determined there was no fire 
stack said adding the cause of the smoke was under investigation 
