nearly four centuries after explorer henry 
hudson sailed up the river that bears his name a replica of his 
ship the half moon will journey down the hudson river on its 
maiden journey 
the new half moon with a crew of 20 will set out downriver on 
its shakedown cruise this coming saturday making an overnight stop 
in new york city andrew hendricks who conceived the project 
announced saturday 
the crew will then sail it down the atlantic coast on a twoweek 
cruise to the ships new home at washington nc on the western 
side of pamlico sound hendricks said plans for future voyages are 
undecided he said 
the half moon was built to honor the netherlands contributions 
to america and hudsons 1609 voyage up the river when the english 
explorer was working for the dutch east india co 
the 85foot 120ton replica is a little different from hudsons 
halve maen this half moon features such nonauthentic features 
as an emergency engine and contemporary navigational equipment 
you play a fine line with the historical thing said 
hendricks citing constraints such as coast guard regulations 
but its as historically accurate as it can be 
the ship originally was set to embark on a tour of several 
northeastern ports on july 5 but the june death of the ships 
architect and chief builder nicholas benton who fell from the 
mast of another ship forced a change of plans 
we had blueprints but it didnt say what some of the sizes 
of the parts were or the colors hendricks said 
hendricks also had to hire people to do work that benton would 
have done for free boosting the cost from 1 million to about 12 
million he said 
