<TEXT>
claudio abbado musical director of the vienna 
state opera was chosen sunday to succeed the late herbert von 
karajan as chief conductor of the berlin philharmonic orchestra 
abbado 56 was selected in a secret ballot by the berlin 
philharmonic orchestras 120 musicians and accepted the post in a 
telephone conversation anke martiny west berlins chief cultural 
official told reporters 
abbado who will be only the fifth chief conductor in the 
107yearold statesubsidized berlin philharmonic was not 
considered among the favorites for the post 
other musical luminaries such as lorin maazel james levine 
daniel barenboim and riccardo muti were initially thought to have 
better chances in the musicians first direct balloting for a new 
leader 
karajan who headed the berlin philharmonic for 35 years died 
july 16 at age 81 the brilliant and revered maestro stirred 
millions of people with his music and was perhaps the worlds most 
honored and prolific conductor 
austrianborn karajan resigned his conductor for life post 
in april after contract differences with the orchestra 
abbado a native of milan italy is considered among the 
worlds top conductors and has made guest appearances with the 
berlin philharmonic since 1966 
no date was immediately set for him to take up his new position 
since he is still bound by contract to the vienna opera martiny 
said negotiations will not be easy but she added a great 
musical future is opening up for berlin 
abbado a member of an artistically inclined family began 
studying piano composition and conducting at milans conservatory 
at age 16 
he also took cello and organ courses and his teachers included 
viennese conductor hans swarovsky 
abbado quickly rose to prominence in the 1960s won prizes and 
led several european and american orchestras then he returned 
home where he became chief conductor at milans la scala opera in 
1968 and later musical director 
he has been the chicago philharmonics chief guest conductor 
since 1982 and he has long worked with the vienna philharmonic and 
london symphony orchestra 
he has been musical director at the vienna state opera since 
1986 
abbado is known for his recordings of modern composers like 
gustav mahler and bela bartok as well as innovative productions of 
operas like giuseppe verdis don carlos 
in public statements he rebelled against what he considered 
bourgeois hesitation to accept modern classical music though he was 
avowedly apolitical he staged free concerts for italian workers 
saying he wanted to reach out to new audiences 
