a pharmaceutical maker on sunday voluntarily 
began the recall of a generic antibiotic used to treat urinary 
tract infections a day after the federal food and drug 
administration requested the action 
the fda contends that bolar pharmaceutical co inc based in 
copiague cheated on product safety tests when it submitted the 
drug nitrofurantoin for fda approval 
